T1  - Strategic Group Dynamics
AU  - Mascarenhas, Briance
Y1  - 1989/06/01
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256365
DO  - 10.5465/256365
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 333
EP  - 352
VL  - 32
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A longitudinal study was conducted of strategic group dynamics over periods of economic stability, growth, and decline in international offshore oil-drilling. Some changes in group strategy were observed during economic growth and decline. Mobility rates among groups were observed to be higher during economic decline than during stability or growth; mobility was also higher between similar groups than between dissimilar groups. The number of groups remained to a large extent the same for an extended period, with the formation of only one additional group. The conditions leading to the formation of this new group are documented.
AB  - A longitudinal study was conducted of strategic group dynamics over periods of economic stability, growth, and decline in international offshore oil-drilling. Some changes in group strategy were observed during economic growth and decline. Mobility rates among groups were observed to be higher during economic decline than during stability or growth; mobility was also higher between similar groups than between dissimilar groups. The number of groups remained to a large extent the same for an extended period, with the formation of only one additional group. The conditions leading to the formation of this new group are documented.
